OL,4,CAgnes Sithole: The woman who fought
OL,5,CSouth Africa's sexist marriage laws
OL,6, Agnes Sithole has become an unlikely
OL,7, hero for hundreds of thousands of black
OL,8, women in South Africa.
OL,10,FAt 72, she took her husband to court to
OL,11,Fstop him selling their home against her
OL,12,Fwishes - and in the process took on
OL,13,Fdecades-old apartheid-era laws to keep
OL,14,Fwhat was rightfully hers.
OL,16,FWith hindsight, Agnes Sithole knew her
OL,17,Fmarriage would be difficult. She
OL,18,Fmarried Gideon, her high-school
OL,19,Fsweetheart in 1972, but quickly found
OL,20,Fherself turning a blind eye to what
OL,21,Fwould become decades of infidelity.
